# Merge into main by default

When a unit of work is complete (feature, fix, or docs) and pushed on a PR branch:

1. Open or update the pull request targeting **`main`**
2. Mark the PR ready (not draft) when it is meant to ship
3. **Merge into `main`** (merge commit is fine unless the repo standard differs)
4. Delete the remote feature branch after merge when appropriate
5. Fast-forward local `main` with `git checkout main && git pull origin main`

Do this by default at the end of a completed task — do not leave finished work sitting only on a feature branch.

## Exceptions

- The user explicitly says not to merge, or to keep it as draft/review-only
- CI is failing and the failure is real (fix or unblock first)
- The change is exploratory and the user has not asked to ship it
